EmailTemplate.subject: Salesforce User Interface Update + Partner Community Access!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hi {!Receiving_User.FirstName},
We wanted to give you an early heads-up that when you log in to salesforce on June 22nd, you will notice a slight change to the user interface experience.
What can you expect? • You will see a new black bar across the top of your screen as shown in the screen shot below. • You can access the Salesforce Partner Community by dropping down the menu in the top left of the screen. • You can continue to access your user menu for salesforce in the top right of the screen.
What’s in it for you? • You gain visibility into which resources and assets are available to Partners and can direct them with confidence.
Who will have access to the Salesforce Partner Community? • All Internal Salesforce users
For more information on this change or to learn more about the Salesforce Partner Community, please see the attached.
If you have any questions, please connect with a Partner Manager or partners@adaptiveinsights.com!
Regards, Rebekah
